This project is the UCSC Anthropology Portal — a Google Apps Script web app for administering department processes. TEST-ONLY deployment: no production data, no migration concerns. The Apps Script project is the source of truth; project knowledge files are a snapshot and may lag — ask me to confirm which version is current if it matters. ARCHITECTURE: Shell + pluggable modules. Index.html/_Scripts.html provide login, nav, and a single server gateway dispatch(module, action, payload) in Code.gs, which validates the module, checks roles, calls the handler, and writes the audit log. The module registry lives in the Modules sheet tab (key, label, icon, roles, handler, include, order, enabled), not in code. A handler name must appear in BOTH getModuleHandler() and getRegisteredHandlers() in Code.gs, and ONLY when its .gs file is actually in the project — otherwise "X is not defined" errors. Deploying code does not add the Modules sheet row; new modules are registered via Admin → Modules. The module key is the dispatch identifier and is permanent. ROLES & IDENTITY: Roles are identity categories (super_admin, staff, senate_faculty, lecturer, graduate_student, undergraduate_student, visitor), not permission levels — never a generic "admin" role. Access is module-centric: each module's Roles list controls entry; finer permissions are per-action checks in handlers, always including super_admin. Profiles are platform-level (Auth.gs): Email, FirstName, LastName, AltNames (JSON array of alternate spellings for matching, not display), Roles, StudentID (7 digits), EmployeeID (8 digits), Active, Notes. Display names are computed (name = "First Last", nameLastFirst = "Last, First"). PersonMatch.gs matches incoming records email-first, then either ID; fills empty ID slots and attaches alt names on certain matches; conflicts are flagged, never silently overwritten. The ImportPolicy allowlist (Admin → Roles) governs which roles a delegated manager/importer may assign — shared by batch import, individual user management, and request approval scoping. CONVENTIONS: Read sheet columns by header name, not position. Module UI objects are declared window.X = (...) (never const — module scripts re-execute on each load). In HTML templates: no bare < or > inside <? ?> scriptlets (use forEach/ includes); use <?!= ?> (force-print) when injecting JSON into <script>. Notes fields and altNames are preserved on update unless explicitly supplied. Syntax-check every .gs via node --check before delivery; verify every onclick handler is exported from its UI object. Configuration is UI-managed (Module Manager, Roles, Import permissions, Request notifications) — avoid telling the user to edit sheets directly except Config.gs constants. Functional/shared email addresses are used for notification destinations; humans always log in with personal accounts. setUp() in Setup.gs creates missing tabs/headers only — it never modifies existing tabs. /dev serves latest saved code; /exec requires a new deployment version (Deploy → Manage deployments → Edit → New version). OPEN THREADS: Thesis module — fully designed (multi-stage workflow: student → advisor → conditional honors review → undergraduate advisor; PDF upload to a configurable Drive folder; filename 2026-Spring_<StudentID>-THES_Last-First.pdf; separate clean database sheet; resubmission replaces in place keeping the Drive file ID) but NOT built — waiting on the user's PDF form to define fields. ThesisModule registration in Code.gs stays commented out until its file ships. Conflict review queue — PersonMatch conflicts currently skip-with-reason in import previews; a reviewable queue (workable by delegated importers) is planned.

